3) Pull strategy (V1 implementation)

You want three modes: oldest-first, priority-first, downstream blocked avoidance. Implement as a scoring + filter pipeline.

A) Inputs from Kanban task card

Minimum fields you’ll likely have:

created_at, updated_at

lane (Backlog/In Progress/Done)

priority (P0..P3 or numeric)

tags (BD/research/ops/admin; “blocked”; “dependency:task123”)

owner (optional)

acceptance_criteria (text)

links[] (docs/PR/files)

checklist_total, checklist_done

blocked_by[] (explicit, preferred)

blockers_count (derived)

B) Candidate filtering (hard rejects)

Reject if:

Not in allowed lanes/tags for this agent

Already leased/locked by another agent (unless expired)

Missing required fields (policy-dependent)

Blocked (if downstream blocked avoidance is enabled)

C) Scoring (soft ordering)

Define a score (higher wins):

score = wP*priority + wA*age + wU*staleness - wB*blocked_penalty - wR*risk_penalty

Where:

priority: map P0=100, P1=50, P2=20, P3=5

age: time since created (or since entered backlog)

staleness: time since last update (captures neglected items)

blocked_penalty: huge if blocked_by nonempty

risk_penalty: optional in V1 (e.g., tasks requiring external posting)

Mode configs

Oldest-first: wA high, wP low

Priority-first: wP high, wA medium

Downstream blocked avoidance: enforce filter blocked_by empty OR set wB extremely high

D) Tie-breakers

Higher priority

Older created_at

Older updated_at (staler wins)

Deterministic hash(task_id) for stability

4) Lease/lock TTL (prevent double-claim)
A) Model

A lease is a time-bounded lock:

lease_owner_agent_id

lease_acquired_at

lease_expires_at

lease_token (random UUID to avoid “stale unlock”)

B) Behavior

Acquire: atomic compare-and-set on task card (or DB) only if lease_expires_at < now or empty.

Renew: agent heartbeats “I’m still working” every X minutes, extending expiry.

Release: agent sets lease empty if done or handing off.

Expiry: if agent dies, lease naturally expires → another agent can claim.

C) TTL values (V1 pragmatic)

Since your run intervals go up to 24h, TTL must be independent of schedule.

Default lease TTL: 45–90 minutes

Heartbeat renew: every 5–10 minutes while working

Hard max lease age: e.g., 6 hours unless task explicitly long-running

Expose in UI:

TTL default, renew cadence, max lease age

5) “Stuck detection” → auto-release / hand-off
A) Define “no updates”

A task is “stuck” if:

Lease exists AND

now - last_task_update_by_agent > N_minutes

“Update” can be:

Kanban comment

checklist tick

artifact link added

status step update

heartbeat “still working” + progress marker (preferred)

B) Actions (V1 simple escalation ladder)

At N minutes stuck:

Ping Discord: “Task T-123 stuck, last progress 47m ago”

After N + grace:

Auto-release lease

Add Kanban comment “Auto-released due to inactivity threshold”

After repeated stuck episodes (count >= K):

Auto-hand-off: move to a “Needs attention” lane/tag; optionally assign to a different agent role

C) Recommended defaults

N = 30–60 min (depends on typical work unit)

grace = 10 min

K = 2 stuck cycles before “Needs attention”

Expose in UI per agent:

stuck threshold N

grace period

max stuck cycles before escalation lane/tag

